Content:
[telegram] <JamPhish> Bitcoin as a Currency has failed.  The Governments and Enterprises are calling it a Comodity.  For that, it will be treated as such.  Bitcoin has too large a Market Cap currently for Private Investors to really move it.  We will see Wall Street eventually rule Bitcoin by issuing BTC to Oil, BTC to Gold, BTC to Wheat, BTC to Uranium . . . it will become a globally accepted store of value - that's it.  
Lightning Network only handles 2% of transactions and ONLY Functions in a Non-Hostile Environment.  Also, Lightning relies on TRUSTED Master Nodes who act as a care taker of funds - legally - this would have to  be a trusted 3rd Party and do a KYC for each user.  In addition, Lightning Requires Sender / Receiver to always be online for transactions to go thru - this is very limiting.  Also, enough transactions have been lost in Lightning, to scare anyone who would ever wish to send a large Sum.  Also, Lightning's method of account is essentially a digital fractional reserve banking system . . . we already have fractional reserve banking - this is the main reason peeps went toward crypto (re @Crypto: Ok tell me!)
